##HTML: <header >{{#c}}</header>
msgid "The King of KingsBy R. J. RushdoonyMarch 26, 2007"
msgstr ""

##HTML: <p >{{#c}}</p>
msgid "California Farmer 261:8 (Nov. 17, 1984), p. 19."
msgstr ""

##HTML: <p >{{#c}}</p>
msgid "Paul, in 1 Timothy 6:15, speaks of Jesus Christ as “the blessed and only Potent"
"ate, the King of kings, and Lord of lords.” Ernest Gordon translated the latter"
" part of this verse as “the King of those kinging it, the Lord of those lording"
" it.” Behind all the powers of history, in other words, stands the Great King, "
"Jesus Christ."
msgstr ""

##HTML: <p >{{#c}}</p>
msgid "This Great King allows men and nations to pursue their evil dreams and to work "
"out their sins. Thus, what men in their evil imaginations see as the solution t"
"o man’s problems becomes in time their curse. The storms of history then in due"
" time sweep away all things that are not founded on the Rock. As Paul says in H"
"ebrews 12:22–29, the things which are all around us, and we ourselves, are bein"
"g shaken so that only those things which cannot be shaken may remain."
msgstr ""

##HTML: <p >{{#c}}</p>
msgid "We must therefore expect crises which will shake us. They will come from the Gr"
"eat King to test us and to prove us. We have no right to expect God to treat us"
" as fragile cut glass."
msgstr ""

##HTML: <p >{{#c}}</p>
msgid "Isaac Watts, in his great hymn “Am I a Soldier of the Cross?” (1724), asked,"
msgstr ""

##HTML: <div >{{#c}}</div>
msgid "Must I be carried to the skies On flow’ry beds of ease, While others fought to "
"win the prize, And sailed through bloody seas?"
msgstr ""

##HTML: <p >{{#c}}</p>
msgid "Watts then said, “Sure I must fight if I would reign,” and he prayed for courag"
"e to endure as a good soldier of Christ."
msgstr ""

##HTML: <p >{{#c}}</p>
msgid "We are in a time of shaking. The Great King is allowing men and nations to purs"
"ue their course to its deadly end. We shall be shaken. The question we need to "
"ask ourselves is this: are we earthquake-proof? Are we so grounded in Christ th"
"at we cannot be shaken?"
msgstr ""

